2. Optimization: Get 100% of your low-end hardware

Solutions that i found:

- Install zRAM (Better RAM management):
It compresses data in your RAM to avoid using the slow SSD/HDD swap.

Ubuntu / Debian:
sudo apt install zram-tools

Arch Linux:
sudo pacman -S zram-tools

- Hardware Acceleration (Fixing Software Rendering):
If your CPU is doing the GPU's job, your PC will be slow and hot. You need the right drivers.

Intel GPU:
Ubuntu/Debian: sudo apt install intel-media-driver-non-free
Arch: sudo pacman -S intel-media-driver

AMD GPU (Debian based):
Download the script from AMD website and run:
sudo apt install ./amdgpu-install_*.deb
sudo amdgpu-install -y --usecase=graphics,rocm
sudo usermod -a -G render,video $LOGNAME

 What OS affected: 
Linux based OS (Low-end hardware focus)
